track_notes: Using this path is the fastest way to reach the summit and aloows you to activate some other on a roll. The slope is a bit hard but there is no difficulties; plenty room for antennas and 360 degres free area! nice place to be

Nice walk around this summit,along the crest and part is in forest, in summer, bring a lot of water.
Plenty room to park. Much room on summit for antenna.
This is a nice walk. park at Coaraze, you will discover an old village by your way. plenty room for antenna and nice panorama

Starting from Langarvin Village, there is a car park. The walk is on a good path, until the end when you reach the ridge; you must take care. Plenty room on summit for antenna. On the way back, you can use the same track, dont forget to visit the old village date from year 1500!
